# Meta Direct Webhooks → Spectral Soundworks

## What Was Built

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/app/api/ig/meta-webhook/route.ts` | **GET** — Meta verification handshake. **POST** — receives DM events, resolves PSID → username, logs Activity, triggers Novu bell |
| `src/lib/novu.ts` | `triggerIgReplyNotification()` helper |
| `src/app/api/ig/test-notification/route.ts` | Dev shortcut to test Novu without a real DM |

---

## Step 1 — Get a Public URL

Meta can't call `localhost`. Pick one:

### Option A — ngrok (dev/testing)
```bash
# Install once
npm install -g ngrok

# In a separate terminal while your app is running
ngrok http 3000
```
Copy the `https://xxxx.ngrok-free.app` URL. Use this as your base URL below.

> [!NOTE]
> Free ngrok URLs change every restart. You'll need to update the Meta webhook URL each time. For persistent testing, sign up for a free ngrok account and get a static domain.

### Option B — Deploy (production)
Use your deployed URL (Vercel, Railway, etc.) — no ngrok needed.

---

## Step 2 — Create a Meta Developer App

1. Go to **[developers.facebook.com](https://developers.facebook.com)** → **My Apps → Create App**
2. Select app type: **Business**
3. Fill in name (e.g. `Spectral Soundworks`) and contact email → **Create App**

---

## Step 3 — Add the Instagram Product

1. In your new app → **Add Products** → find **Instagram** → **Set Up**
2. Under Instagram → **API Setup with Instagram Business Login**
3. Click **Generate Token** next to your Instagram Business account
4. Copy the token → paste into `.env.local`:
   ```
   META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_token_here
   ```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This token expires. For production, generate a **Long-Lived Token** or use a System User token. See [Meta docs on token types](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/instagram-platform/instagram-graph-api/get-started#access-tokens).

---

## Step 4 — Configure the Webhook

1. In your Meta App → left sidebar → **Webhooks**
2. Select object type: **Instagram**
3. Click **Subscribe to this object**
4. Fill in:

   | Field | Value |
   |---|---|
   | **Callback URL** | `https://YOUR_PUBLIC_URL/api/ig/meta-webhook` |
   | **Verify Token** | `spectral_ig_verify_2024` (matches your `.env.local`) |

5. Click **Verify and Save** — Meta will call `GET /api/ig/meta-webhook` and check the challenge. Your route handles this automatically.

---

## Step 5 — Subscribe to the `messages` Field

After verifying, you'll see a list of subscription fields:

1. Find **`messages`** → click **Subscribe**
2. Also subscribe to **`messaging_optins`** (optional but recommended)

That's it — Meta will now POST to your webhook whenever someone replies to your DMs.

---

## Step 6 — Add Your Instagram Account to the App

1. In your Meta App → **Instagram → Accounts**
2. Add your Instagram Business account
3. Make sure the account has the `instagram_manage_messages` permission granted

---

## Step 7 — Fill In Your Novu Secret Key

The notification won't fire without this:

1. Go to **[dashboard.novu.co](https://dashboard.novu.co)** → **API Keys**
2. Copy your **Secret Key**
3. Add to `.env.local`:
   ```
   NOVU_SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here
   ```

---

## Step 8 — Create the Novu Workflow

1. Novu Dashboard → **Workflows → Create Workflow**
2. Set the **Workflow Identifier** (slug) to exactly: **`ig-reply-received`**
3. Add step → **In-App**
4. Set body to:
   ```
   @{{instagramHandle}} replied: "{{messageSnippet}}"
   ```
5. **Publish** the workflow

---

## Step 9 — Test the Full Pipeline

### Test Novu (no real DM needed):
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ig/test-notification \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"artistName":"Beach House","instagramHandle":"beachhouse","messageSnippet":"Would love to connect!"}'
```
→ Bell icon should light up in your sidebar immediately.

### Test the Meta webhook handler:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ig/meta-webhook \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "object": "instagram",
    "entry": [{
      "id": "123",
      "messaging": [{
        "sender": { "id": "SENDER_PSID" },
        "recipient": { "id": "PAGE_ID" },
        "timestamp": 1234567890,
        "message": { "mid": "MSG_123", "text": "Hey! This sounds awesome." }
      }]
    }]
  }'
```
→ Check server logs for `[meta-webhook] Incoming DM` and notification trigger.

